Here’s a carefully curated list of top resources for learning VMware, broken down by Video Series, Documents, and Community:

⸻

🎥 Video Series
	1.	Pluralsight – VMware vSphere Data Center Virtualization (VCP-DCV)
	•	Deep coverage of ESXi, vCenter, VM management, networking, and storage.
	•	Tailored for VCP certification.
	•	pluralsight.com
	2.	LinkedIn Learning – VMware vSphere Essential Training
	•	Great for beginners; covers setup, VM provisioning, templates, and clustering.
	•	Taught by VMware expert Rick Crisci.
	3.	vSphere YouTube Channel
	•	VMware vSphere Official
	•	Includes webinars, new feature demos, and VMworld talks.
	4.	David Bombal (YouTube) – VMware Labs
	•	Free labs, networking with VMware, and NSX basics.
	•	David Bombal’s Channel
	5.	INE – VMware Learning Paths
	•	More advanced topics like NSX, Horizon, and vSAN.
	•	ine.com

⸻

📄 Documents
	1.	VMware vSphere Documentation (Official)
	•	The most comprehensive and up-to-date technical references.
	•	VMware Docs
	2.	VMware Hands-on Labs Guidebooks
	•	Free, practical, and aligned with real-world environments.
	•	labs.vmware.com
	3.	VMware Validated Designs
	•	Architecture and best practices for deploying large-scale VMware environments.
	•	Ideal for enterprise engineers and consultants.
	4.	“Mastering VMware vSphere” Book Series by Scott Lowe
	•	Industry-standard book for learning VMware from ground up.
	•	Highly recommended for home labs and certification study.
	5.	VMware Learning Guides
	•	Found on the VMware Learning Zone.
	•	Step-by-step study guides and exam blueprints.

⸻

🌐 Community
	1.	VMware Technology Network (VMTN)
	•	VMTN Forums
	•	Official support forum with subtopics for each product.
	2.	r/vmware (Reddit)
	•	Real-world discussions, home lab setups, certification advice.
	•	r/vmware
	3.	VMware Discord & Slack Groups
	•	Community-driven chat for immediate help and networking.
	•	Example: VMUG Discord
	4.	VMUG (VMware User Group)
	•	Local and global chapters, webinars, discounts on exams and training.
	•	www.vmug.com
	5.	Twitter/X Hashtags
	•	Try #vExpert, #VMware, #vSphere for active conversations and event news.

